{:title "Fix Workflow Artifact Persistence Bug"
 :description
 "The workflow system generates code artifacts in-memory but fails to persist
  them to disk. The release phase completes with :success false and 0 files
  written, yet the workflow continues and marks all phases as completed. This
  was discovered during dogfooding when the integration spec generated code but
  wrote nothing to the filesystem.

  Root causes:
  1. Artifact handoff between phases fails - verify phase receives no code
  2. Release phase doesn't actually write files to disk
  3. Tests don't validate that files were written
  4. Silent failure - workflow continues despite :success false

  This is a critical bug that prevents any workflow from producing actual results."

 :intent
 {:type :bug-fix
  :scope ["components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/runner.clj"
          "components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/implement.clj"
          "components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/verify.clj"
          "components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/release.clj"
          "components/artifact/src/ai/miniforge/artifact/interface.clj"
          "components/workflow/test/ai/miniforge/workflow/artifact_persistence_test.clj"]}

 :constraints
 ["Fix must be backward compatible with existing workflows"
  "Tests must validate actual file system changes"
  "Fail loudly and early when artifact persistence fails"
  "Verify phase must fail if it receives no code artifact"
  "Release phase must fail if it writes 0 files"
  "Add integration test that runs full workflow and checks files exist"
  "All existing tests must continue to pass"]

 :workflow/type :standard-sdlc
 :workflow/version "2.0.0"

 :plan/tasks
 [{:task/id :analyze-artifact-flow
   :task/description
   "Trace artifact flow through workflow phases to find where persistence breaks.

    Investigate:
    - How implement phase creates and stores code artifacts
    - How artifacts are passed to verify phase (currently failing)
    - How release phase retrieves artifacts for writing
    - Where in the flow does the artifact get lost

    Read files:
    - components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/runner.clj (phase execution)
    - components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/implement.clj (artifact creation)
    - components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/release.clj (file writing)
    - components/artifact/src/ai/miniforge/artifact/interface.clj (storage)

    Document:
    - Current artifact flow diagram
    - Where handoff fails
    - Why verify phase gets no artifact
    - Why release writes 0 files"
   :task/type :design
   :task/dependencies []}

  {:task/id :fix-phase-artifact-handoff
   :task/description
   "Fix artifact passing between phases so verify/release receive the code.

    In components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/runner.clj:
    - Ensure implement phase result includes :artifact in context
    - Pass context with artifact to next phase
    - Validate artifact exists before calling next phase
    - Log artifact metadata (file count, size) for debugging

    In components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/implement.clj:
    - Ensure code artifact is stored in execution context
    - Return artifact in phase result map
    - Add validation that artifact was created

    Expected result:
    - Verify phase receives non-empty :artifact in context
    - Release phase can retrieve artifact for writing
    - Context flows correctly: implement -> verify -> release"
   :task/type :implement
   :task/dependencies [:analyze-artifact-flow]}

  {:task/id :add-verify-phase-validation
   :task/description
   "Make verify phase fail loudly if it receives no code artifact.

    In components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/verify.clj:
    - Check if context contains :artifact or :phase/result/artifact
    - If no artifact found, throw descriptive error
    - Error message: 'Verify phase received no code artifact from implement phase'
    - Include debugging info: what keys ARE in context, what phase completed
    - Don't mark verify as 'completed' if validation fails

    This prevents silent failures where verify says 'I don't see any code'
    but still marks itself as completed."
   :task/type :implement
   :task/dependencies [:fix-phase-artifact-handoff]}

  {:task/id :fix-release-phase-file-writing
   :task/description
   "Fix release phase to actually write artifact files to disk.

    In components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/release.clj:
    - Retrieve code artifact from context/phase result
    - For each file in artifact.code/files:
      - Write to filesystem at correct path
      - Create parent directories if needed
      - Handle :create, :modify, :delete actions
    - Return metrics with actual files-written count
    - Fail if artifact has files but 0 were written

    Integration with artifact store:
    - Check if artifact store has the code
    - Pull from store if not in direct context
    - Ensure file paths are absolute or relative to project root

    Expected result:
    - Files physically exist on disk after release
    - Metrics show files-written > 0 for successful release
    - git status shows modified/created files"
   :task/type :implement
   :task/dependencies [:add-verify-phase-validation]}

  {:task/id :add-release-phase-validation
   :task/description
   "Add validation that release phase actually persisted files.

    In components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/release.clj:
    - After writing files, verify they exist on filesystem
    - Read back at least one file to confirm write succeeded
    - If files-written = 0 but artifact had files, throw error
    - Error: 'Release phase failed to persist N files from artifact'
    - Mark release as :failed not :completed when this happens

    Return enriched metrics:
    - :files-written (count of successfully written files)
    - :files-verified (count verified to exist post-write)
    - :bytes-written (total size)
    - :paths-written (list of file paths for debugging)"
   :task/type :implement
   :task/dependencies [:fix-release-phase-file-writing]}

  {:task/id :add-workflow-success-validation
   :task/description
   "Make workflow fail loudly when phases complete but :success is false.

    In components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/runner.clj:
    - After all phases complete, check final :success flag
    - If :success is false, throw error with phase details
    - Include which phase failed, what the error was
    - Don't just return {:success false} quietly

    Also check:
    - If :files-written = 0 but workflow type expects code, warn or fail
    - If any phase marked :failed, workflow should fail
    - Aggregate phase errors into workflow error message

    This prevents workflows from 'completing' when they actually failed."
   :task/type :implement
   :task/dependencies [:add-release-phase-validation]}

  {:task/id :add-artifact-persistence-tests
   :task/description
   "Add integration tests that validate files are actually written.

    Create: components/workflow/test/ai/miniforge/workflow/artifact_persistence_test.clj

    Tests:
    1. test-full-workflow-writes-files
       - Run complete workflow with simple spec
       - Verify files exist on filesystem after completion
       - Check git status shows changes
       - Read file contents to verify correctness

    2. test-verify-fails-without-artifact
       - Mock implement phase to return empty artifact
       - Verify phase should throw error, not complete
       - Workflow should fail with descriptive message

    3. test-release-fails-with-zero-files-written
       - Mock release phase to return :files-written 0
       - Should throw error about persistence failure
       - Workflow should fail, not mark as completed

    4. test-workflow-fails-when-success-false
       - Mock phase to complete with :success false
       - Workflow should throw error, not return quietly
       - Error message should include phase details

    These tests should have caught the bug we found in dogfooding."
   :task/type :test
   :task/dependencies [:add-workflow-success-validation]}

  {:task/id :add-phase-result-validation-tests
   :task/description
   "Add unit tests for phase-level artifact validation.

    In existing test files, add:

    components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/implement_test.clj:
    - Test that implement phase returns :artifact in result
    - Test that artifact contains :code/files
    - Test error when implementation produces no code

    components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/verify_test.clj:
    - Test verify fails when context has no :artifact
    - Test verify succeeds when artifact is present
    - Test error message is descriptive

    components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/release_test.clj:
    - Test release writes files to temp directory
    - Test release returns correct :files-written count
    - Test release fails when artifact has files but write fails
    - Test release verifies files exist after writing"
   :task/type :test
   :task/dependencies [:add-artifact-persistence-tests]}

  {:task/id :update-artifact-store-interface
   :task/description
   "Ensure artifact store properly persists and retrieves code artifacts.

    In components/artifact/src/ai/miniforge/artifact/interface.clj:
    - Review store-artifact! and get-artifact functions
    - Ensure artifacts persist correctly to store
    - Add validation that retrieved artifacts match what was stored
    - Add :artifact/type tag to distinguish code vs other artifacts

    If artifact store is working correctly but not being used:
    - Update workflow runner to explicitly use artifact store
    - Store artifact after implement phase
    - Retrieve artifact in verify/release phases
    - Add logging for store/retrieve operations"
   :task/type :implement
   :task/dependencies [:analyze-artifact-flow]}

  {:task/id :add-workflow-debugging-instrumentation
   :task/description
   "Add logging and debugging output to trace artifact flow.

    Add debug logging at each handoff point:
    - Implement phase: 'Storing artifact with N files'
    - Between phases: 'Passing artifact to next phase: keys=...'
    - Verify phase: 'Received artifact with N files' or 'ERROR: No artifact'
    - Release phase: 'Writing N files from artifact'
    - Post-release: 'Verified N files exist on disk'

    Add to workflow result:
    - :debug/artifact-trace (list of artifact transitions)
    - :debug/phase-contexts (what each phase received)
    - :debug/files-written-paths (actual paths written)

    This makes debugging future artifact issues much easier."
   :task/type :implement
   :task/dependencies [:fix-phase-artifact-handoff]}

  {:task/id :test-with-dogfooding-spec
   :task/description
   "Re-run the original integration spec to verify fix works.

    Steps:
    1. Run: miniforge run integrate-dag-into-workflow.spec.edn
    2. Verify workflow completes with :success true
    3. Verify files exist: git status shows modifications
    4. Verify file contents are correct
    5. Verify metrics show files-written > 0

    If successful:
    - The original dogfooding attempt should now work
    - Files should be written to disk
    - Workflow should complete successfully

    This validates the fix end-to-end with the spec that revealed the bug."
   :task/type :test
   :task/dependencies [:add-artifact-persistence-tests
                       :add-phase-result-validation-tests
                       :add-workflow-debugging-instrumentation]}]}
